parameters:
\n<Guild Master>Ah, the hero... Oops, my apologies. We mustn't let on in
this place, right.

\n<Guild Master>I've heard about your situation. Please leave the search for
Lady Pirika to us. In the meantime, it would be a great help
if you could assist with the requests from this town.

\n<Guild Master>Also, I've been informed that Lady Pirika's father will
cover all the inn expenses. Please don't worry about it.

\n<Guild Master>Imp Cave infested with succubi? Could there have been a
mistake in the request? We'll investigate the cause on our
end as well.

\n<Guild Master>Regarding Lady Pirika's matter, we've received information
from a merchant who dealt with someone matching her
description. It seems they traded in decorative items.

\n<Guild Master>She must have earned enough for her stay. Whether it's at an
inn or a vacant house... either way, it seems she is indeed
hiding out in Anis.

\n<Guild Master>There's still no sighting information on Pirika-sama. The
gatekeepers have been informed, so we should know if she
leaves town. It's highly likely she's still in hiding.

\n<Guild Master>Sigh... \n[1]-sama, please continue to handle quests for a
little while longer. We will surely find Pirika-sama.

\n<Adventurer>I wonder what kind of person the hero is. They say they
swing a huge sword and cut monsters in two with a single
stroke. They must be a muscular macho man, no doubt about
it.

\n<Adventurer>There are no decent quests. The rewards aren't worth the
difficulty.

\n<Adventurer>Thanks to us taking down monsters, this town is safe, you
know? And yet, that idiot king goes and skimps on the
budget.

\n<Adventurer>The rewards are half of what they were a year ago. Tch. As
if we're not risking our lives for this job.
\n<Adventurer>Munch munch. Gulp gulp... Ahh-.

\n<Adventurer>Anise's liquor really is delicious. It's almost like I work
just to drink.

\n<Adventurer>Even if monsters don't come into town, we still need to
clean up the surroundings. You never know when they might
form a group and attack.

\n<Adventurer>A drink before work is the best. A drink after work is even
better. And I'll drink during work too!
